modules.description: This module provides infix operators for vector operations like element access, mapping, appending, and flat mapping, supporting both safe and unsafe variants. It works directly with vector types that have read or write capabilities, enabling expressive chaining of transformations and effectful operations. Use this module to write concise vector manipulations with familiar operator syntax, such as using `>>=` for flat mapping or `@` to concatenate vectors.
The module enables creation and manipulation of polymorphic dynamic arrays with read/write access, offering indexed element operations, resizing
